{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/background-information/prevalence/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"e8fd2377-deba-5e27-9879-c44fb6974ce6","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 342bf248-851f-4ec7-93c9-17e40e02dfe5 --><h2>How common is it?</h2><!-- end field 342bf248-851f-4ec7-93c9-17e40e02dfe5 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item a8df6e9a-9eee-4ed3-b573-714dbd74ecf6 --><!-- begin field 137e7540-7ac2-4039-b437-951e7a51eb61 --><ul><li><strong>Travellers' diarrhoea is the most common health problem encountered by travellers</strong> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">WHO, 2012</a>].<ul><li>It most commonly affects people travelling from areas of high standards of hygiene and sanitation to less developed destinations [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">WHO, 2012</a>]. </li><li>It is thought that travellers' diarrhoea occurs in 20–90% of people travelling for up to two weeks in low- or middle-income countries [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">CATMAT, 2015</a>]. The prevalence is influenced by the destination and season of travel [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">CDC, 2017a</a>]. </li><li>Incidence of travellers' diarrhoea is age-dependent. Infants and toddlers have the highest incidence rates [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">Ashkenazi et al, 2016</a>]. </li><li>Travellers' diarrhoea is equally prevalent in men and women, although it is more common in young adults than older people [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">CDC, 2017a</a>]. </li><li>There is a seasonal variation, with less episodes of travellers' diarrhoea occurring in winter [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">Steffen, 2015</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers/references/\">Steffen, 2017</a>]. </li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 137e7540-7ac2-4039-b437-951e7a51eb61 --><!-- end item a8df6e9a-9eee-4ed3-b573-714dbd74ecf6 -->","topic":{"id":"d5cf1db6-a6d9-54fb-b393-095d8af57067","topicId":"9042b194-f66e-44c6-a91c-76ffa626e3e8","topicName":"Diarrhoea - prevention and advice for travellers","slug":"diarrhoea-prevention-advice-for-travellers","lastRevised":"Last revised in February 2019","chapters":[{"id":"3f7bee04-88e6-5a40-86d5-e39dc29e4059","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"47ddb819-f046-5e92-999c-a3d47a00ede8","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"bdd3d81e-da2b-5807-b257-8dd4d73a596c","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"5ac4ad9d-b3fb-51c6-84de-19181b30e02c","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"5568a30c-164d-5d4f-8d41-ad7eff1173cb","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"6f04e901-40c5-5906-a7eb-5935a99758bb","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"e0f32109-cb0a-51e3-aa59-bcac4a364a5f","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"4a74f052-b6c8-5743-b69f-30ffc630174e","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"81c43095-b29a-537e-ad23-56ca74d2e6fb","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criter